@node english
@{b}
                       Only for not italian people
@{ub}

PD notice
=========

ClipTranslator v.1.0 is public domain, which means this program may be
freely  distributed.   It  is  not allowed to sell ClipTranslator (for
more  than the usual amount of money asked for a PD disk) unless there
is  an  agreement  with Author.  Of course gifts in the form of money,
own  made  software,  hardware or anything else are always welcome and
appreciated.

Short description of program
============================

ClipTranslator  is  designed for italian users, but it can be used also
by other people with some tricks.
With  this  program you can translate a selected text, from English to
italian.   The selected text must be before copied in the clipboard by
pressing Amiga+C.
The  translation  is  provided  by  an external program:  ITAL 2.0+ by
Arturo Ortino that translates entirely a text file.

If  you want use my program for the translation of clipboard text from
English to deutch (or other) you need a program that translates a text
file in your desired language and saves it on a selectable file.  This
program must have a Arexx interface.  In this case you must modify the
file ClipTranslator.rexx that invoced the translation program.
This  is  not  very  simple  to do.  If you want that I support others
translation programs please contact me by e-mail.


Requirements:
=============

ClipTranslator use MUI interface and Arexx.

- AmigaOS 2.0+ (Tested only on OS 3.0 and 3.1)
- CPU 68020+
- ITAL 2.0+
- MUI 3.6+
- MUI/BetterString.mcc
- iffparse.library

Author: Paolo Stefanucci

HomePage: http://www.geocities.com/Vienna/5354
Mirror:   http://www.livenet.it/woc
e-mail:   woc.bbs@napoli.netway.it

